This testimony is true. Therefore rebuke them sharply, that they may be sound by faith; not giving heed to Jewish fables, and commandments of men whom turn from the truth... They profess to know God, but I'm works they deny him, being abominable, disobedient, and disqualified for every good work. For if I make you sorrowful, then whom is he that makes me glad but the one who is made sorrowful by me?? This punishment which was inflicted by the majority is sufficient for such a man; so that on the contrary you ought rather to forgive and comfort him, least perhaps such a one be swallowed up with too much sorrow. Therefore I urge you to reaffirm your love to him. I might put you to the test, whether you are obedient in all things. For if indeed I have forgiven anything, I have forgiven that one for your sales in the presence of Christ. Who, contrary to hope, in hope believed. But the eyes of the wicked Will fail, and they shall not escape; and their hope-lost of life...
